Put a large #saucepan{} of water with @salt{1/2%tsp} on to boil for the pasta.

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @Echalion shallot{1}. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Trim the @courgette{1}. Use a #peeler{} to peel long ribbons down the length of the courgette, stopping at the spongy centre.

Finely chop the @chives{1}(finely chopped) (use #scissors{} if easier). Zest and halve the @lemon{1/2}.

Once boiling, add the @rigatoni pasta{180%g} to the water and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

When ready, reserve some of the pasta water (see pantry for amount), then drain in a #colander{}.

Pop the pasta back into the pan, drizzle with @oil{} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

== Garlicky Greens ==

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium heat.

Once hot, add the courgette ribbons and season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}. Cook until softened, ~{2-3%minutes}, then stir in the garlic and cook for ~{1%minute} more.

Add the @baby spinach{100%g} a handful at a time and cook until wilted and piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Once cooked, transfer everything to a large #bowl{} and cover to keep warm.

== Chicken and Sauce ==

Put your (now empty) frying pan back on medium heat with a drizzle of @oil{}. Once hot, add the @diced chicken breast{260%g} and fry until browned all over, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Add the shallot to the chicken and cook, stirring occasionally, until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Stir in the @vegetable stock paste{10%g} and @reserved pasta water{100%ml}, then simmer until reduced by half, ~{3-4%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging. The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Mix in the @creme fraiche{150%g} and heat through until piping hot, then season with @ground black pepper{}. Stir through the chives and three quarters of the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g}.

== Assembly ==

Stir the cooked pasta through your sauce along with half the greens. Add a splash of @water{} if it's a little too thick.

Add a pinch of lemon zest and a squeeze of lemon juice. Taste and add more lemon juice, salt and pepper if needed.

Share the creamy pasta between your #bowls{} and top with the remaining greens.

Finish with a sprinkle of the remaining hard Italian style cheese.

Enjoy!